properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 20 at 10:25AM AKST until February 21 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions. Whiteout conditions occurring with
visibilities frequently less than one quarter mile. Additional
snow accumulations of up to 5 inches. Winds gusting as high as
45 mph.

* WHERE...Along the coast and Nunivak Island.

* WHEN...Until noon AKST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow are creating whiteout conditions.
The dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could
cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST FRIDAY FOR THE COAST AND NUNIVAK ISLAND
